#: ../../../topics/selectors.rst:541
msgid "Selector examples on HTML response"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/selectors.rst:543
msgid ""
"Here's a couple of :class:`Selector` examples to illustrate several "
"concepts. In all cases, we assume there is already an :class:`Selector` "
"instantiated with a :class:`~scrapy.http.HtmlResponse` object like this::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/selectors.rst:547
msgid "sel = Selector(html_response)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/selectors.rst:549
msgid ""
"Select all ``<h1>`` elements from a HTML response body, returning a list of :"
"class:`Selector` objects (ie. a :class:`SelectorList` object)::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/selectors.rst:552
msgid "sel.xpath(\"//h1\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/selectors.rst:554
msgid ""
"Extract the text of all ``<h1>`` elements from a HTML response body, "
"returning a list of unicode strings::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/selectors.rst:557
msgid ""
"sel.xpath(\"//h1\").extract()         # this includes the h1 tag\n"
"sel.xpath(\"//h1/text()\").extract()  # this excludes the h1 tag"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/selectors.rst:560
msgid "Iterate over all ``<p>`` tags and print their class attribute::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/selectors.rst:562
msgid ""
"for node in sel.xpath(\"//p\"):\n"
"    print node.xpath(\"@class\").extract()"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/selectors.rst:566
msgid "Selector examples on XML response"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/selectors.rst:568
msgid ""
"Here's a couple of examples to illustrate several concepts. In both cases we "
"assume there is already an :class:`Selector` instantiated with a :class:"
"`~scrapy.http.XmlResponse` object like this::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/selectors.rst:572
msgid "sel = Selector(xml_response)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/selectors.rst:574
msgid ""
"Select all ``<product>`` elements from a XML response body, returning a list "
"of :class:`Selector` objects (ie. a :class:`SelectorList` object)::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/selectors.rst:577
msgid "sel.xpath(\"//product\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/selectors.rst:579
msgid ""
"Extract all prices from a `Google Base XML feed`_ which requires registering "
"a namespace::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/selectors.rst:582
msgid ""
"sel.register_namespace(\"g\", \"http://base.google.com/ns/1.0\")\n"
"sel.xpath(\"//g:price\").extract()"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/selectors.rst:588
msgid "Removing namespaces"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/selectors.rst:590
msgid ""
"When dealing with scraping projects, it is often quite convenient to get rid "
"of namespaces altogether and just work with element names, to write more "
"simple/convenient XPaths. You can use the :meth:`Selector.remove_namespaces` "
"method for that."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/selectors.rst:595
msgid "Let's show an example that illustrates this with Github blog atom feed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/selectors.rst:597
msgid "First, we open the shell with the url we want to scrape::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/selectors.rst:599
msgid "$ scrapy shell https://github.com/blog.atom"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/selectors.rst:601
msgid ""
"Once in the shell we can try selecting all ``<link>`` objects and see that "
"it doesn't work (because the Atom XML namespace is obfuscating those nodes)::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/selectors.rst:604
msgid ""
">>> response.xpath(\"//link\")\n"
"[]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/selectors.rst:607
msgid ""
"But once we call the :meth:`Selector.remove_namespaces` method, all nodes "
"can be accessed directly by their names::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/selectors.rst:610
msgid ""
">>> response.selector.remove_namespaces()\n"
">>> response.xpath(\"//link\")\n"
"[<Selector xpath='//link' data=u'<link xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2005/"
"Atom'>,\n"
" <Selector xpath='//link' data=u'<link xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2005/"
"Atom'>,\n"
" ..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/selectors.rst:616
msgid ""
"If you wonder why the namespace removal procedure is not always called, "
"instead of having to call it manually. This is because of two reasons which, "
"in order of relevance, are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/selectors.rst:620
msgid ""
"Removing namespaces requires to iterate and modify all nodes in the "
"document, which is a reasonably expensive operation to performs for all "
"documents crawled by Scrapy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/selectors.rst:624
msgid ""
"There could be some cases where using namespaces is actually required, in "
"case some element names clash between namespaces. These cases are very rare "
"though."
msgstr ""
